    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Expanded NATO And New Russia; The Real Game</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert C Cox letter disputes Thomas L Friedman's March 31 Op-Ed column opposing expansion of NATO (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Gulf of Tonkin II'' (column, March 31): The liberal and conservative arguments for NATO outlined by Thomas L. Friedman are a smokescreen for the real game. If a heavily lobbied Senate approves NATO expansion, American arms makers stand to gain billions of dollars from the sale of weapons. Clearly, this policy initiative does not have to do with what is good for the United States but with what is good for a powerful few.</p>
        <p>ROBERT C. COX  Milford, Conn., April 1, 1998</p>
      </block>
